<subSubSection id="91CD80F6D724525C9090A56EFA136F8B" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="D968D37DD724525C9090A56EFC876F24" blockId="10.[491,856,357,381]" box="[491,856,357,381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">
<heading id="82206411D724525C9090A56EFC876F24" box="[491,856,357,381]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED724525C9090A56EFC876F24" authority="Zacher, 1913" authorityName="Zacher" authorityYear="1913" box="[491,856,357,381]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Tetranychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludeni">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C9090A56EFC876F24" bold="true" box="[491,856,357,381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C9090A56EFD176F24" bold="true" box="[491,712,357,381]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">Tetranychus ludeni</emphasis>
Zacher, 1913
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D968D37DD724525C9090A59CFA136F8B" blockId="10.[491,1529,407,673]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">
The red mite, 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED724525C93FAA593FD016FF6" authorityName="Zacher" authorityYear="1913" box="[641,734,407,431]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Tetranychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludeni">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C93FAA593FD016FF6" box="[641,734,407,431]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">T. ludeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is widespread in the centre and south of mainland 
<collectingCountry id="A1C093EDD724525C9450A59CFA576FF6" box="[1323,1416,407,431]" name="Portugal" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C94EDA59CFDC26F8B" author="Carmona M. M." pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="221 - 230" refId="ref8289" refString="Carmona M. M. 1960. Contribuicao para o conhecimento dos acaros das plantas cultivadas em Portugal - I. Agronomia Lusitana, 22: 221 - 230." type="journal article" year="1960">Carmona 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C9353A5B1FCEF6F8B" author="Carmona M. M. &amp; Dias J. S." box="[552,816,442,466]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref8584" refString="Carmona M. M., Dias J. S. 1980. O complexo Acarina nas culturas portuguesas. In: Actas do I Congresso Portugues de Fitiatria e Fitofarmacologia, Lisboa. p. 97 - 115." type="book chapter" year="1980">Carmona and Dias 1980</bibRefCitation>
). It is also common on the 
<collectingRegion id="1B131D9FD724525C9536A5B1FB476F8B" box="[1101,1176,442,466]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">Azores</collectingRegion>
archipelago, namely on FAI,
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91CD80F6D724525C9090A5D6FCCD6CF8" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" type="description">
<paragraph id="D968D37DD724525C9090A5D6FA076C60" blockId="10.[491,1529,407,673]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">
PIC and SMG (
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C93E0A5D6FC786FAC" author="Costa-Comelles J. C. &amp; Soares A. &amp; Schanderl H. J. &amp; Vercher, R. E. &amp; Ferragut F." box="[667,935,477,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="40 - 44" refId="ref8832" refString="Costa-Comelles J. C., Soares A., Schanderl H. J., Vercher, R. E., Ferragut F. 1993. A contribution to data on mite fauna in Azores islands. Faial: Relatorios e Comunicacoes do Departamento de Biologia da Universidade dos Acores, Faial / 93, 22: 40 - 44." type="journal article" year="1993">
Costa-Comelles 
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C923AA5D5FCA56FAC" box="[833,890,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C92CAA5D6FB596FAC" author="Borges P. A. &amp; Vieira V. &amp; Amorim I. R. &amp; Bicudo N. &amp; Fritzen N. &amp; Gaspar C. &amp; Heleno R. &amp; Hortal J. &amp; Lissner J. &amp; Logunov D. &amp; Machado A. &amp; Marcelino J. &amp; Meijer S. S. &amp; Melo C. &amp; Mendonca E. P. &amp; Moniz J. &amp; Pereira F. &amp; Santos A. S. &amp; Simoes A. M. &amp; Torrao E." box="[945,1158,477,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" refId="ref7953" refString="Borges P. A., Vieira V., Amorim I. R., Bicudo N., Fritzen N., Gaspar C., Heleno R., Hortal J., Lissner J., Logunov D., Machado A., Marcelino J., Meijer S. S., Melo C., Mendonca E. P., Moniz J., Pereira F., Santos A. S., Simoes A. M., Torrao E. 2010. List of arthropods (Arthropoda). In: Borges P. A., Costa" type="book" year="2010">
Borges 
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C956FA5D5FB936FAC" box="[1044,1100,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), and on 
<collectingRegion id="1B131D9FD724525C9589A5D6FA896FAC" box="[1266,1366,477,501]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">Madeira</collectingRegion>
Island, where it attacks local banana plantations causing damage to the fruits (
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C95C8A5F4FA986C4E" author="Carmona M. M." box="[1203,1351,511,535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="469 - 482" refId="ref8554" refString="Carmona M. M. 1992. Acaros fitofagos e predadores da Ilha da Madeira - II. Boletin Sanidad Vegetal, Plagas, 18: 469 - 482." type="journal article" year="1992">Carmona 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C9428A5F4FD546C63" author="Carmona M. M. &amp; Dias J. S." pageId="10" pageNumber="389" refId="ref8624" refString="Carmona M. M., Dias J. S. 1996. Fundamentos de Acarologia Agricola. Lisboa: Fundacao Calouste Gulbenkian. pp. 423." type="book" year="1996">Carmona and Dias 1996</bibRefCitation>
). This polyphagous mite can be found on several important agricultural crops,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D968D37DD724525C9090A64FFCCD6CF8" blockId="10.[491,1529,407,673]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">
but particularly on bean, 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED724525C9380A64EFCAA6C05" box="[763,885,580,604]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Phaseolus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C9380A64EFCAA6C05" box="[763,885,580,604]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">P. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C9207A64FFB586C05" author="Carmona M. M. &amp; Dias J. S." box="[892,1159,580,604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref8584" refString="Carmona M. M., Dias J. S. 1980. O complexo Acarina nas culturas portuguesas. In: Actas do I Congresso Portugues de Fitiatria e Fitofarmacologia, Lisboa. p. 97 - 115." type="book chapter" year="1980">Carmona and Dias 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD724525C95E8A64FFA1F6C05" author="Ferreira M. A. S. &amp; Carmona M. M." box="[1171,1472,580,604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" pagination="111 - 118" refId="ref9638" refString="Ferreira M. A. S., Carmona M. M. 1994. Acarofauna do feijoeiro em Portugal. Boletin Sanidad Vegetal, Plagas, 20: 111 - 118." type="journal article" year="1994">Ferreira and Carmona 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED724525C93F8A663FD006C26" authorityName="Zacher" authorityYear="1913" box="[643,735,615,639]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Tetranychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludeni">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD724525C93F8A663FD006C26" box="[643,735,615,639]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="389">T. ludeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very frequent in the INIAV acarological collection, with new plant hosts presented in 
<tableCitation id="9455E6C6D724525C93CDA682FCD36CF8" box="[694,780,649,673]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[119,175,505,526]" captionText="Table 1 Review of spider mite (Tetranychidae) species and new host records in mainland Portugal, the Azores and Madeira archipelagos, discerning the source of information." pageId="10" pageNumber="389">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
